headline: Carrier Global’s Quiet Dividend Strategy Deserves Attention
summary: Mastercard just distributed $0.87 per share to shareholders on February 9, 2026, marking the payment network’s latest quarterly dividend. While the 14.5% year-over-year increase from $0.76 continues an impressive growth streak, the dividend’s modest yield and conservative payout strategy reveal a company prioritizing buybacks over income generation. headline: Visa Confronts Fee Pressures As New Payment Alternatives Gain Ground
summary: Merchant groups led by major retailers are seeking greater involvement in the long running U.S. interchange fee settlement with Visa before court approval. In Europe, the European Payments Initiative has rolled out a broad regional payments alternative aimed at reducing reliance on Visa and other U.S. processors. These parallel developments highlight regulatory, competitive and geopolitical pressures that could influence Visa's long term role in global payments. Visa (NYSE:V) enters these...
